# 2026-07-13: ephemeral, single-use "go ahead and buy this" markers -- Claude
# creates one only in direct response to the user explicitly confirming a
# specific buy, and each script deletes its own immediately after executing.
# Not meant to persist or show up in history (unlike the deliberate on/off
# markers noted below), so they're plain machine state, not tracked.
.ENTRY_CONFIRMED_*

# NOTE: .verdict_log.jsonl IS tracked on purpose (unlike the *_state.json
# bookkeeping above) -- it's the raw history of every gradable local verdict,
# the actual data grade_verdicts.py's accuracy scorecard is built from.

# NOTE: .SATELLITE_BUYING_PAUSED and .DISABLE_AUTOSTART are deliberate on/off
# markers with explanatory content (like a kill-switch) — tracked in git on
# purpose, not listed here, so their presence/removal is visible in history.
# (.LONGHOLD_ENTRY_PAUSED, used briefly on 2026-07-13, was superseded same-day
# by the broader .ENTRY_CONFIRMED_* standing policy above and removed.)

# logs
*.log

# python cache
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# ephemeral daily refresh
today.md

# external skill clones (installed fresh by install-trader-stack.sh; not our code)
ai-berkshire/
financial-services/
serenity-skill/
